The paper presents a framework for edge-aware optimization that improves performance for a variety of computer vision problems, including stereo, depth super-resolution, and render from defocus. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages properties of the domain transform, a method for edge-aware filtering, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the computational complexity and parallelizability of the method, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a novel optimization method, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
